answerText: Bingham plastics [or viscoplastic; do not accept "pseudo-plastic"][10] The tau in two-paramater rheological models such as the Bingham plastic model stands for this quantity that is related to gamma, the shear rate.

question: Question: A common one of these fluids can be created by mixing corn starch and water. For 10 points each: [10] Name these non-Newtonian fluids which follow a namesake singly eponymous model in which they have a linear tau-gamma relationship after an initial threshold for tau is reached.
